Note:
WORK-STEALING DEQUE - Per-thread deque with work-stealing.

Single-owner-pushes-and-pops-from-bottom, multiple-stealers-take-from-top.
Based on the Chase-Lev deque algorithm. Atomic ordering uses the in-tree
atomic_core.runa primitives: relaxed loads/stores on the owner's bottom
index, sequentially-consistent CAS on the stealer top index, and acquire
fences around steal/take to preserve the Chase-Lev consistency invariants.

WSQ layout (32 bytes):
  offset 0:  bottom_index     (8 bytes) - owner thread reads/writes
  offset 8:  top_index        (8 bytes) - stealers CAS this
  offset 16: buffer_ptr       (8 bytes) - circular buffer of task pointers
  offset 24: buffer_capacity  (8 bytes) - capacity (power of 2)

The buffer stores task pointers. Owner enqueues at bottom (incrementing),
dequeues from bottom (decrementing). Stealers steal from top via CAS.

Dependencies:
- core/atomic_core.runa
- memory/layout.runa
:End Note

Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/atomic_core.runa" as Atomic
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Memory
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/memory_core.runa" as Mem

Constant WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM as Integer is 0
Constant WSQ_OFF_TOP as Integer is 8
Constant WSQ_OFF_BUFFER as Integer is 16
Constant WSQ_OFF_CAPACITY as Integer is 24
Constant WSQ_STRUCT_SIZE as Integer is 32

Constant WSQ_OK as Integer is 1
Constant WSQ_ERR_INVALID as Integer is 0
Constant WSQ_ERR_FULL as Integer is -1
Constant WSQ_EMPTY as Integer is 0
Constant WSQ_ABORT as Integer is -2

@Reasoning
Create a fixed-capacity work-stealing queue. The capacity must be a power
of two so we can use bitwise-and instead of modulo for index masking.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Allocate the WSQ record and a buffer of capacity * 8 bytes. Initialize
top and bottom to zero. The caller is responsible for ensuring capacity
is a power of two; we round non-power-of-two values up.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
The capacity is fixed - no resize. Choose a capacity that comfortably
exceeds expected concurrency level.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Stored task pointers must remain valid until they are popped or stolen.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "wsq_round_up_pow2" takes n as Integer returns Integer:
    If n is less than or equal to 1:
        Return 1
    End If
    Let p be 1
    While p is less than n:
        Set p to p multiplied by 2
    End While
    Return p
End Process

Process called "wsq_create" takes capacity as Integer returns Integer:
    Let cap be proc wsq_round_up_pow2 with capacity
    If cap is less than 2:
        Set cap to 2
    End If

    Let q be proc allocate from Memory with WSQ_STRUCT_SIZE
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let buffer_bytes be cap multiplied by 8
    Let buffer be proc allocate from Memory with buffer_bytes
    If buffer is equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Memory with q
        Return 0
    End If

    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_TOP, 0
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_BUFFER, buffer
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_CAPACITY, cap
    Return q
End Process

Process called "wsq_destroy" takes q as Integer returns Integer:
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return WSQ_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_BUFFER
    If buffer is not equal to 0:
        proc deallocate from Memory with buffer
    End If
    proc deallocate from Memory with q
    Return WSQ_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Owner pushes a task at the bottom. Returns OK on success or FULL if the
buffer is at capacity.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load bottom, load top with acquire, check that bottom - top < capacity,
write task at buffer[bottom & mask], release-store new bottom.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Single owner - no CAS required. One acquire load + one release store.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must be the owning thread.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "wsq_push" takes q as Integer, task_ptr as Integer returns Integer:
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return WSQ_ERR_INVALID
    End If
    Let bottom be proc atomic_load_relaxed from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM)
    Let top be proc atomic_load_acquire from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_TOP)
    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_CAPACITY
    Let size be bottom minus top
    If size is greater than or equal to capacity:
        Return WSQ_ERR_FULL
    End If

    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_BUFFER
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let idx be bottom bitwise and mask
    Let offset be idx multiplied by 8
    proc memory_set_int64 from Mem with buffer, offset, task_ptr

    proc atomic_store_release from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM), (bottom plus 1)
    Return WSQ_OK
End Process

@Reasoning
Owner pops a task from the bottom. Returns 0 if the queue is empty, or
the task pointer on success.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Decrement bottom (relaxed), full fence, load top. If bottom < top the
queue is empty; restore bottom and return 0. If bottom == top there is
exactly one task and we race with a stealer via CAS on top. Otherwise the
task is ours.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Most pops are uncontended (single owner). The CAS occurs only when the
queue has exactly one element.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Caller must be the owning thread.
@End Security_Scope

Process called "wsq_pop_local" takes q as Integer returns Integer:
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let old_bottom be proc atomic_load_relaxed from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM)
    Let new_bottom be old_bottom minus 1
    proc atomic_store_seq_cst from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM), new_bottom

    proc memory_barrier_seq_cst from Atomic

    Let top be proc atomic_load_relaxed from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_TOP)
    If new_bottom is less than top:
        Note: Queue empty - restore bottom
        proc atomic_store_relaxed from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM), top
        Return 0
    End If

    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_CAPACITY
    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_BUFFER
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let idx be new_bottom bitwise and mask
    Let offset be idx multiplied by 8
    Let task_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with buffer, offset

    If new_bottom is greater than top:
        Return task_ptr
    End If

    Note: Exactly one element - race with stealer
    Let cas_ok be proc atomic_compare_and_swap from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_TOP), top, (top plus 1)
    If cas_ok is equal to 1:
        proc atomic_store_relaxed from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM), (top plus 1)
        Return task_ptr
    End If

    Note: Stealer won the race
    proc atomic_store_relaxed from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM), (top plus 1)
    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning
Steal a task from the top of another thread's queue. Returns the stolen
task pointer or 0 if empty/aborted.
@End Reasoning

@Implementation
Load top (acquire), load bottom (acquire). If empty return 0. Read task
at top, CAS top forward. If CAS fails, another stealer beat us.
@End Implementation

@Performance_Hints
Steal contention can be high under fan-out. Backoff in caller if many
consecutive steals fail.
@End Performance_Hints

@Security_Scope
Stealable from any thread except the owner (owner uses wsq_pop_local).
@End Security_Scope

Process called "wsq_steal" takes q as Integer returns Integer:
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let top be proc atomic_load_acquire from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_TOP)
    proc memory_barrier_seq_cst from Atomic
    Let bottom be proc atomic_load_acquire from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM)

    If top is greater than or equal to bottom:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let capacity be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_CAPACITY
    Let buffer be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with q, WSQ_OFF_BUFFER
    Let mask be capacity minus 1
    Let idx be top bitwise and mask
    Let offset be idx multiplied by 8
    Let task_ptr be proc memory_get_int64 from Mem with buffer, offset

    Let cas_ok be proc atomic_compare_and_swap from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_TOP), top, (top plus 1)
    If cas_ok is equal to 1:
        Return task_ptr
    End If
    Return 0
End Process

Process called "wsq_size" takes q as Integer returns Integer:
    If q is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let bottom be proc atomic_load_acquire from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_BOTTOM)
    Let top be proc atomic_load_acquire from Atomic with (q plus WSQ_OFF_TOP)
    Let size be bottom minus top
    If size is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return size
End Process
